---
description: Performance rules for desktop workflows
globs: ["src/**/*", "src-tauri/src/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Performance is a core product feature.

Rules:
- do not block the UI for expensive operations
- lazy load heavy panels where appropriate
- virtualize long lists such as commit history
- avoid unnecessary full refreshes
- memoize only when justified by actual rendering cost
- cache short-lived expensive results when useful
- keep AI requests cancellable when possible

Important hotspots:
- repository open
- status refresh
- commit history rendering
- diff parsing/rendering
- branch list updates
- AI explain/review actions

Do not:
- rerender large trees from trivial state changes
- refetch unrelated data after simple mutations
- parse giant diffs synchronously in the UI if avoidable